## Getting Started

1. Clone this repo
{% if archetype == 'python' -%}
2. Install dependencies: `uv sync`
{% elif archetype == 'dotnet' -%}
2. Restore packages: `dotnet restore`
{% elif archetype == 'generic' -%}
2. Install dependencies (see your package manager docs)
{% endif -%}
3. Set up the pre-commit hook: `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`
4. Open the project with your agentic coding tool
5. Start building — use `/plan` before implementing, `/new-decision` for choices

## Framework

This project uses the [Agentic Coding Framework](https://github.com/your-org/agentic-framework)
(v{{ framework_version }}) for decision tracking, session continuity, and quality gates.

Key commands:
- `/plan` — architecture plan before implementing
- `/new-decision` — record a design choice as an ADR
- `/qa` — run quality checks before committing
- `/handoff` — write a session handoff note
- `/health` — check framework integrity

See `docs/CONTEXT_GUIDE.md` for the full context-layer model.
